       5. SECURITY CONCERNS

       CRITICAL:

       1. OTP Exposed in Logs (auth.service.ts, line 106)
       console.log(`mocked email sent ${otp}`)  // OTP visible in logs!
       1. One of the worst security issues - OTP should never be logged.
       2. Timing-Based Email Enumeration (auth.service.ts, line 87-92)
       forgetPassword: if(!user) return  // Attacker knows email doesn't exist
       2. No delay, allows username enumeration with simple requests.
       3. No Rate Limiting on Auth Endpoints
         - No brute-force protection on /login, /register, /forget-password
         - Attackers can try unlimited password combinations
       4. Password Reset Without Email Verification (auth.service.ts, line 87-107)
         - Sends OTP via email but no email confirmation mechanism
         - If email service fails, user locked out

       HIGH:

       5. Missing CSRF Protection
         - No CSRF tokens on forms
         - Only relies on sameSite: "lax" cookies
       6. Insufficient Password Requirements (auth.dto.ts)
         - Error message claims "one number" required, but validation has minNumbers: 1
         - Actually requires 1 symbol minimum but message doesn't mention it
       7. No Account Lockout After Failed Attempts
         - User can try unlimited login attempts
       8. JWT Stored in Cookies Without Expiry Validation
         - maxAge set correctly but no refresh token rotation
         - Old refresh tokens can still be used after logout
       9. Environment Variables Not Validated for Production (env.ts)
         - No check that secrets are long enough (bcrypt salt rounds could be 4!)

       MEDIUM:

       10. Missing SQL Injection Protection in Some Queries (users.repo.ts, line 31)
       db.raw(`SELECT EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM USERS WHERE email=? OR phone=? ) AS "exists"`, [email, phone])
       // Using raw() with parameterized queries is OK, but error-prone
       11. No HTTPS Redirect in Development (auth.controller.ts, line 19)
       secure: env.NODE_ENV === "production"  // Dev uses insecure cookies!
       12. User Password Hash Exposed in Responses
         - Not returned but good hygiene to explicitly exclude
         - DTOs don't explicitly exclude sensitive fields

