 Redis Key Convention

 rt:{sha256(rawRefreshTokenJWT)}  →  "{dbRecordId}"   TTL = token remaining seconds

 Storing the DB record id as the value lets us skip a lookup when rotating tokens.
 The raw JWT is never stored — only its hash (same principle as OTP hashing).

